{"timestamp": "2026-07-25T03:06:12.623584", "tool_name": "edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "C:\\SovereignAI\\Docs\\Workflow-Automation-Hooks.md", "old_string": "## Total Token Savings Impact\n\n### Per-Session Savings\n- **Documentation Loading**: ~1,700 tokens (every session)\n- **Gate Verification**: ~600-900 tokens (per workflow execution)\n- **Structure Validation**: ~2,000 tokens (per consistency check)\n- **Phase Permission**: ~200-400 tokens (per operation)\n\n### Estimated Annual Savings\nAssuming 10 sessions per day, 5 workflow executions per session, 2 consistency checks per week, 100 operations per session:\n\n- **Documentation Loading**: 1,700 \u00c3\u2014 10 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **6,205,000 tokens/year**\n- **Gate Verification**: 750 \u00c3\u2014 5 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **1,368,750 tokens/year**  \n- **Structure Validation**: 2,000 \u00c3\u2014 2 \u00c3\u2014 52 = **208,000 tokens/year**\n- **Phase Permission**: 300 \u00c3\u2014 100 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **10,950,000 tokens/year**\n\n**Total Estimated Annual Savings: ~18,731,750 tokens**", "new_string": "## Total Token Savings Impact\n\n### Per-Session Savings\n- **Documentation Loading**: ~1,700 tokens (every session)\n- **Gate Verification**: ~600-900 tokens (per workflow execution)\n- **Structure Validation**: ~2,000 tokens (per consistency check)\n- **Phase Permission**: ~200-400 tokens (per operation)\n- **Template Compliance**: ~800-1,200 tokens (per workflow file creation)\n- **Agent Doc Completeness**: ~500-800 tokens (per agent documentation update)\n- **Cross-Reference Integrity**: ~300-500 tokens (per cross-reference operation)\n- **Session State Management**: ~400-600 tokens (per session)\n- **Log File Organization**: ~200-300 tokens (per log operation)\n- **Configuration Validation**: ~300-400 tokens (per configuration change)\n- **Dependency Checking**: ~500-700 tokens (per dependency change)\n- **Quality Metrics Calculation**: ~600-800 tokens (per workflow completion)\n- **Audit Trail Generation**: ~200-400 tokens (per operation)\n- **Workflow Progress Tracking**: ~400-600 tokens (per workflow step)\n\n### Estimated Annual Savings\nAssuming 10 sessions per day, 5 workflow executions per session, 2 consistency checks per week, 100 operations per session, 5 workflow file creations per session, 2 agent documentation updates per week, 10 cross-reference operations per session, 10 log operations per session, 3 configuration changes per session, 2 dependency changes per session, 5 workflow completions per session, 10 workflow steps per session:\n\n- **Documentation Loading**: 1,700 \u00c3\u2014 10 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **6,205,000 tokens/year**\n- **Gate Verification**: 750 \u00c3\u2014 5 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **1,368,750 tokens/year**  \n- **Structure Validation**: 2,000 \u00c3\u2014 2 \u00c3\u2014 52 = **208,000 tokens/year**\n- **Phase Permission**: 300 \u00c3\u2014 100 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **10,950,000 tokens/year**\n- **Template Compliance**: 1,000 \u00c3\u2014 5 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **1,825,000 tokens/year**\n- **Agent Doc Completeness**: 650 \u00c3\u2014 2 \u00c3\u2014 52 = **67,600 tokens/year**\n- **Cross-Reference Integrity**: 400 \u00c3\u2014 10 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **1,460,000 tokens/year**\n- **Session State Management**: 500 \u00c3\u2014 10 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **1,825,000 tokens/year**\n- **Log File Organization**: 250 \u00c3\u2014 10 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **912,500 tokens/year**\n- **Configuration Validation**: 350 \u00c3\u2014 3 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **383,250 tokens/year**\n- **Dependency Checking**: 600 \u00c3\u2014 2 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **438,000 tokens/year**\n- **Quality Metrics Calculation**: 700 \u00c3\u2014 5 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **1,277,500 tokens/year**\n- **Audit Trail Generation**: 300 \u00c3\u2014 100 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **10,950,000 tokens/year**\n- **Workflow Progress Tracking**: 500 \u00c3\u2014 10 \u00c3\u2014 365 = **1,825,000 tokens/year**\n\n**Total Estimated Annual Savings: ~39,695,600 tokens**"}, "success": true}
{"timestamp": "2026-07-25T03:06:22.135115", "tool_name": "edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "C:\\SovereignAI\\Docs\\Workflow-Automation-Hooks.md", "old_string": "## Testing Results\n\nAll hooks have been tested individually with simulated input data:\n\n### Option 1 Test\n```\nInput: SessionStart event\nOutput: Successfully loaded Architect agent rules and templates\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 2 Test\n```\nInput: PostToolUse read on Rules/Architect/Architect_Rules.md\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Gate 1 PASS: Governance context established, rules loaded\nInput: PostToolUse write on Workflow/Architect/test_workflow.md  \nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Gate 2 PASS: Plan structure created, template compliance verified\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 3 Test\n```\nInput: PreToolUse write to Agents/Architect/AGENTS.md\nOutput: Permission granted (valid naming)\nInput: PreToolUse write to Agents/Architect/agents.md\nOutput: Permission denied (invalid naming, exit code 2)\nInput: PreToolUse write to Workflow/invalid_directory/test.md\nOutput: Permission denied (invalid workflow naming, exit code 2)\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 4 Test\n```\nInput: PreToolUse read to Rules/Architect/Architect_Rules.md\nOutput: Permission granted (phase_0 allows read)\nInput: PreToolUse write to Scripts/test.py\nOutput: Permission granted (phase_0 allows Scripts/ creation)\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```", "new_string": "## Testing Results\n\nAll 14 hooks have been tested individually with simulated input data:\n\n### Option 1 Test\n```\nInput: SessionStart event\nOutput: Successfully loaded Architect agent rules and templates\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 2 Test\n```\nInput: PostToolUse read on Rules/Architect/Architect_Rules.md\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Gate 1 PASS: Governance context established, rules loaded\nInput: PostToolUse write on Workflow/Architect/test_workflow.md  \nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Gate 2 PASS: Plan structure created, template compliance verified\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 3 Test\n```\nInput: PreToolUse write to Agents/Architect/AGENTS.md\nOutput: Permission granted (valid naming)\nInput: PreToolUse write to Agents/Architect/agents.md\nOutput: Permission denied (invalid naming, exit code 2)\nInput: PreToolUse write to Workflow/invalid_directory/test.md\nOutput: Permission denied (invalid workflow naming, exit code 2)\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 4 Test\n```\nInput: PreToolUse read to Rules/Architect/Architect_Rules.md\nOutput: Permission granted (phase_0 allows read)\nInput: PreToolUse write to Scripts/test.py\nOutput: Permission granted (phase_0 allows Scripts/ creation)\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 5 Test\n```\nInput: PreToolUse write to Workflow/Architect/test_workflow.md (missing header)\nOutput: Permission denied (missing required header fields, exit code 2)\nInput: PreToolUse write to Workflow/Architect/test_workflow.md (complete header)\nOutput: Permission granted (template compliance verified)\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 6 Test\n```\nInput: PostToolUse write to Agents/Architect/AGENTS.md (incomplete)\nOutput: \u00e2\u0161\u00a0\u00ef\u00b8\udc8f Warning: Missing industry-standard sections\nInput: PostToolUse write to Agents/Architect/AGENTS.md (complete)\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Documentation completeness verified\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 7 Test\n```\nInput: PostToolUse write to Rules/Architect/test.md (with broken references)\nOutput: \u00e2\u0161\u00a0\u00ef\u00b8\udc8f Warning: Referenced file does not exist\nInput: PostToolUse write to Rules/Architect/test.md (valid references)\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Cross-reference integrity verified\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 8 Test\n```\nInput: SessionEnd event\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Session summary generated, session state updated\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 9 Test\n```\nInput: PostToolUse write to Logs/Architect/test.log\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Log file organized with timestamp, moved to proper directory\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 10 Test\n```\nInput: PreToolUse write to Scripts/Governance/Config/test.json (valid)\nOutput: Permission granted (JSON structure validated)\nInput: PreToolUse write to Scripts/Governance/Config/test.json (invalid)\nOutput: Permission denied (invalid JSON structure, exit code 2)\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 11 Test\n```\nInput: PreToolUse write to Scripts/test.py (with undeclared dependencies)\nOutput: \u00e2\u0161\u00a0\u00ef\u00b8\udc8f Warning: Undeclared dependencies found\nInput: PreToolUse write to Scripts/test.py (all dependencies declared)\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Dependency checking passed\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 12 Test\n```\nInput: PostToolUse write to Workflow/Architect/test_workflow.md\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Quality metrics calculated (Quality: 7/10, Token Cost: 7/10, Efficiency: 6/10)\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 13 Test\n```\nInput: PostToolUse read operation\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Audit trail entry generated with metadata\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```\n\n### Option 14 Test\n```\nInput: PostToolUse write to Workflow/Architect/test_workflow.md\nOutput: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Workflow progress updated, step completion detected\nStatus: \u00e2\u0153\u2026 PASS\n```"}, "success": true}
{"timestamp": "2026-07-25T03:06:25.755025", "tool_name": "edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "C:\\SovereignAI\\Docs\\Workflow-Automation-Hooks.md", "old_string": "### Additional Automation Hooks\n- **Workflow step detection** for automatic progression tracking\n- **Template compliance validation** for all workflow files\n- **Agent documentation completeness** checking\n- **Cross-reference integrity** validation", "new_string": "### Additional Automation Hooks\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Workflow step detection** for automatic progression tracking (implemented as Option 14)\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Template compliance validation** for all workflow files (implemented as Option 5)\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Agent documentation completeness** checking (implemented as Option 6)\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Cross-reference integrity** validation (implemented as Option 7)\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Session state management** (implemented as Option 8)\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Log file organization** (implemented as Option 9)\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Configuration validation** (implemented as Option 10)\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Dependency checking** (implemented as Option 11)\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Quality metrics calculation** (implemented as Option 12)\n- \u00e2\u0153\u2026 **Audit trail generation** (implemented as Option 13)"}, "success": true}
{"timestamp": "2026-07-25T03:06:30.192093", "tool_name": "edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "C:\\SovereignAI\\Docs\\Workflow-Automation-Hooks.md", "old_string": "## Conclusion\n\nThe implementation of these 4 base-level workflow automation hooks provides substantial token savings (estimated ~18.7M tokens annually) while improving quality, consistency, and performance. All hooks have been successfully implemented, tested, and integrated into the existing SovereignAI governance system.\n\nThe hooks follow established patterns, maintain compatibility with existing systems, and provide a foundation for further automation and optimization opportunities.", "new_string": "## Conclusion\n\nThe implementation of these 14 workflow automation hooks provides substantial token savings (estimated ~39.7M tokens annually) while improving quality, consistency, and performance. All hooks have been successfully implemented, tested, and integrated into the existing SovereignAI governance system.\n\nThe hooks follow established patterns, maintain compatibility with existing systems, and provide a foundation for further automation and optimization opportunities. The original 4 base-level hooks address core workflow automation needs, while the 10 additional hooks provide advanced validation, monitoring, and state management capabilities that further reduce token waste and improve system quality."}, "success": true}
